# Pryladova Monorepo

## This file

- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always-on Cursor project rule (`alwaysApply: true`).
- Injected into every agent request in this repo; follow it over generic model habits.
- When editing this file, match its existing format. Do not be overly descriptive.

## Agent Communication

- Terse, technical, no-fluff responses (Caveman-lite).
- Drop filler, pleasantries, hedging.
- Direct answers, code snippets, exact commands only. No yapping.

## Environment & Tooling

- OS: Windows. Terminal: PowerShell.
- Output PowerShell-compatible commands. No Bash-specific syntax.

## Runtime versions

- Never pin or cite Node, pnpm, or dependency versions from memory.
- Repo wins: `package.json` (`engines`, `packageManager`), lockfile.
- Local: `node -v`, `pnpm -v` when tooling targets this machine.
- Upstream: `npm view <pkg> version` before greenfield defaults or version advice.
- After verify: new production work uses Active LTS; not EOL majors (18, 20, …) unless a dependency forces it.
- If not verified, say so — do not invent a version.

## Before changing code

- Read sibling files in app/package; match naming, layout, patterns.
- Smallest correct diff. No refactor/reformat outside scope.
- Stay inside requested app/package.
- Packages disagree → follow local package. Don't "standardize" unasked.

## Docs and comments

- No session-specific fixes, version pins, workarounds, or chat context in repo files.
- Docs state what to run and where config lives — not how we debugged it once.
- Comments: why non-obvious, not what the code already says.
- If a fact belongs in package.json, lockfile, or .env.example — put it there, not in prose.

## Monorepo discipline

- Shared code → shared packages. No copy-paste across apps.
- `packages/*` never imports `apps/*`. Apps never import each other directly.
- Single pnpm workspace, single `pnpm-lock.yaml`. No npm/yarn artifacts.
- Flag new dependencies before adding. No duplicate library where one exists.
- Dependency additions: Always `pnpm --filter <workspace-name> add <pkg>`. Never `npm install`.

## Git

- Never commit, stage, or push. User runs all git ops.
- Active task on X — don't touch unrelated Y (other apps, packages, or files) for commit separation.
- Commit plans should not be overly precise and small.

## TypeScript (.ts/.tsx)

- Explicit types at module boundaries (exports, API handlers, shared utils).
- `const` arrow functions. `handleX` naming for event handlers.
- Early returns over nesting.
- No empty `catch`. No floating promises — `await` or explicit `void`.
- Follow package's existing formatter/linter. No style opinions from this rule.

## Naming

- Filenames: kebab-case (`user-profile.ts`).
- Exports: PascalCase (components/classes), camelCase (functions/variables).

## Quality bar

- Complete, working changes for requested scope only.
- No placeholders, stubs, "wire up later" unless asked.
- Include imports/types/wiring needed to run.
- Shared type/API contract changed → update callers, run typecheck (`pnpm -r typecheck` or local script) before done.

## Env & secrets

- Never commit `.env` or hardcode secrets. New config → existing env-loading pattern.

## Accessibility/UI

- Semantic HTML first. ARIA/keyboard only if native insufficient.
- No default `tabindex`/`role`/`aria-*` on natively-working elements.

## Testing

- No suite/convention yet. Don't assume one, don't add speculative test files, don't skip logic assuming "tests cover it."

## Stack-specific rules

- NestJS/React/shared-Zod-types etc. → separate globbed `.mdc` files. Deferred for now.
